Componentc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://l-jamora.github.io/m150-onto#Component

The taxonomy of components includes the main components of a sewage system according to the advisory leaflet DWA-M 150 and the reference table 128 "Object Types". It is recommended to create individuals for Pipe Sections with the template: ` PipeSection[PipeSectionDesignation] ` ` PipeSection[HG001] ` It is recommended to create individuals for Nodes with the template: ` Node[NodeDesignation] ` ` Node[KG001] ` It is also recommended to declare that Components flows to another component with the asymmetric/irreflexive sub-object property `flowsTo` (Inverse: flowsFrom). The ontology should then automatically reason, that all components flowing to / from each other are connected -- with its transitive super-object property "connectedWith".
is equivalent to
Object Type c
has Reference Table dp value 128
has sub-classes
Node c, Pipe Section c
is in domain of
connected With op, flietVon op, flows To op, inspected In op, rendered By op
is in range of
connected With op, flietVon op, flows To op, inspects op, renders op

Geometryc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://l-jamora.github.io/m150-onto#Geometry

The taxonomy of geometry includes the GIS geometry data of M150-Components. These include Geometry Object and Geometry Points. It is recommended to create individuals for geometric objects with the template: ` GeoObject[PipeSection/Node Designation] ` ` GeoObject[HG001] ` for Pipe Section: Geometry Objects; ` GeoObject[KG001] ` for Node: Geometry Objects. It is recommended to create individuals for geometric points with the template: ` GeoPoint[Geometry Point Description] ` ` GeoPoint[GP001] `. `GeoObject`'s should be declared as the parent of 'GeoPoint''s with the object property `isParentOf`. (Inverse: isChildOf) `GeoObject`'s should be declared as the renderer of a Component with the object property 'renders'. (Inverse: renderedBy)
has sub-classes
Object c
is in domain of
renders op
is in range of
rendered By op

Referencec back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://l-jamora.github.io/m150-onto#Reference

The taxonomy of references includes the reference tables found in the advisory leaflet DWA-M 150. DWA-M 150 categorizes reference tables by type of data. Examples are: - Reference Table 105: Material Types (Class/Subclass: Reference/Material) - Reference Table 202: Condition Assessment Coding Systems (Reference/CodingSystem) Each subclass refers to a specific reference table in DWA-M 150, implied with the equivalentTo axiom "hasReferenceTable value "[RefTableNumber]"". The different types found within a reference table are then listed as subclasses of the aforementioned subclass.

Reportc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://l-jamora.github.io/m150-onto#Report

The taxonomy of reports includes inspection and condition reports for a sewage system, according to the structure of the advisory leaflet DWA-M 150. It is recommended to create individuals for inspection reports with the template: ` Inspection[PipeSectionDesignation]_[Date] `; ` Inspection[HG001]_[HI003] ` for Pipe Section: Inspection reports; ` Inspection[KG001]_[KI003] ` for Node: Inspection reports. It is recommended to create individuals for condition reports within an inspection with the template: ` Condition[PipeSectionDesignation]_[Stationing(ConditionReport)]_[Code] `; ` Condition[HG001]_[HZ001]_[HZ002] ` for Pipe Section: Condition reports; ` Condition[HG001]_[KZ001]_[KZ002] ` for Node: Condition reports. According to the DWA-M 150, the coding systems that can be applied here are: - DIN EN 13508-2 - DWA 149-2 - DWA ATV-M 143 - ISYBAU2001 - ISYBAU1996
has sub-classes
Inspection c
is in domain of
inspects op
is in range of
